{"responsePhase":"analysis_complete","techExplanation":"The component uses a two-panel master-detail layout: a sidebar shows a tree of categories, and the main area shows either a prompt list or detail view depending on selection. State is managed with hierarchical userState and coordinated events for navigation. All data is passed as static arrays; filtering is done in-memory. Child components receive data slices, config, and state via standard props. Event handling uses the coordinated, standardized system. Styling is based on the supplied styles prop, ensuring a pastel, modern UI.","userExplanation":"This tool lets you browse and explore AI prompts organized by categories and subcategories. Use the left sidebar to pick a category. You'll see all prompts in that category, and you can click any prompt to view full details. It's easy to drill in and out, and the clean design helps you focus on the prompts you need.","componentOptions":[{"AIRank":1,"AIRankExplanation":"","option":{"functionalRequirements":"This component provides an interactive, read-only browser for AI prompts, structured by categories and subcategories. Users can navigate a hierarchical sidebar showing all categories and their nested subcategories. Selecting a category displays all AI prompts within it, each showing at least the prompt name and description. Users can click on a prompt to view its complete details, including name, description, status, creation date, and last updated date. The design must be clean, modern, and pastel-themed, focusing on whitespace and easy navigation. Users can smoothly drill-in to deeper levels (from category to prompt) and drill-out (back to list or categories) as needed. No prompt editing or creation is available; the experience is strictly for browsing and viewing.","technicalDesign":"The root component manages overall state: the currently selected category and, if present, the selected prompt. It contains two main panes in a horizontal flex layout: a sidebar for hierarchical category navigation and a main content area for prompts. The sidebar uses a tree view to show categories and subcategories, emitting selection events. The main panel adapts: if a category is selected, it displays a list of prompts (filtered by CategoryID); if a prompt is selected, it displays a detail view. State is managed via useState and hierarchical state paths for child components. All child components receive data slices, config, and userState via the standard interface. Design and layout use the provided styles prop, aligned with the specified pastel, modern look. Event handling is centralized through a standard handler, supporting selection and drill-in/out. All property names match the casing in the sample data.","componentCode":"function createComponent(React, ReactDOM, useState, useEffect, useCallback, createStateUpdater, createStandardEventHandler) {
  'use strict';

  function AIPromptViewer({ data, utilities, userState, callbacks, styles }) {
    // State: selectedCategoryID, selectedPromptID, plus child states
    const [fullUserState, setFullUserState] = useState({
      selectedCategoryID: null,
      selectedPromptID: null,
      sidebar: {},
      promptList: {},
      promptDetail: {},
      ...userState
    });

    const updateUserState = (stateUpdate) => {
      const newState = { ...fullUserState, ...stateUpdate };
      setFullUserState(newState);
      if (callbacks?.UpdateUserState) {
        callbacks.UpdateUserState(newState);
      }
    };

    const handleComponentEvent = (event) => {
      // Handle category selection from sidebar
      if (event.type === 'itemSelected' && event.source === 'CategorySidebar') {
        updateUserState({
          selectedCategoryID: event.payload.itemId,
          selectedPromptID: null, // Reset prompt selection when new category selected
          sidebar: event.payload.newState || fullUserState.sidebar
        });
        return;
      }
      // Handle prompt selection from prompt list
      if (event.type === 'itemSelected' && event.source === 'PromptList') {
        updateUserState({
          selectedPromptID: event.payload.itemId,
          promptList: event.payload.newState || fullUserState.promptList
        });
        return;
      }
      // Handle drill-out/back from detail view
      if ((event.type === 'actionTriggered' && event.payload?.action === 'back' && event.source === 'PromptDetail') || (event.type === 'drillOut' && event.source === 'PromptDetail')) {
        updateUserState({
          selectedPromptID: null
        });
        return;
      }
      // Standard stateChanged event
      const standardHandler = createStandardEventHandler(updateUserState, callbacks);
      standardHandler(event);
    };

    // Data extraction helpers
    const categories = data?.data_item_0 || [];
    const prompts = data?.data_item_1 || [];

    // Filter prompts by selected category (null means show prompts without a CategoryID)
    const filteredPrompts = prompts.filter(p => {
      if (fullUserState.selectedCategoryID == null) {
        return p.CategoryID == null;
      }
      return p.CategoryID === fullUserState.selectedCategoryID;
    });

    // Prompt selected?
    const selectedPrompt = prompts.find(p => p.ID === fullUserState.selectedPromptID);

    // Layout: Sidebar (category tree) | Main panel (prompt list or detail)
    return (
      <div
        style={{
          display: 'flex',
          height: '100%',
          background: styles.colors.background,
          fontFamily: styles.typography.fontFamily
        }}
      >
        {/* Sidebar */}
        <div
          style={{
            width: '320px',
            minWidth: '220px',
            maxWidth: '380px',
            background: styles.colors.surface,
            borderRight: `${styles.borders.width} solid ${styles.colors.border}`,
            padding: styles.spacing.md,
            boxSizing: 'border-box',
            overflow: 'auto',
            height: '100%',
            display: 'flex',
            flexDirection: 'column'
          }}
        >
          <CategorySidebar
            data={categories}
            config={{}}
            userState={fullUserState.sidebar || {}}
            onEvent={handleComponentEvent}
            styles={styles}
            callbacks={callbacks}
            utilities={utilities}
            statePath=\"sidebar\"
            selectedCategoryID={fullUserState.selectedCategoryID}
          />
        </div>
        {/* Main panel */}
        <div
          style={{
            flex: 1,
            overflow: 'auto',
            padding: styles.spacing.lg,
            background: styles.colors.background,
            height: '100%',
            display: 'flex',
            flexDirection: 'column'
          }}
        >
          {!selectedPrompt && (
            <PromptList
              data={filteredPrompts}
              config={{}}
              userState={fullUserState.promptList || {}}
              onEvent={handleComponentEvent}
              styles={styles}
              callbacks={callbacks}
              utilities={utilities}
              statePath=\"promptList\"
              selectedPromptID={fullUserState.selectedPromptID}
            />
          )}
          {selectedPrompt && (
            <PromptDetail
              data={selectedPrompt}
              config={{}}
              userState={fullUserState.promptDetail || {}}
              onEvent={handleComponentEvent}
              styles={styles}
              callbacks={callbacks}
              utilities={utilities}
              statePath=\"promptDetail\"
            />
          )}
        </div>
      </div>
    );
  }

  // <<CHILD_COMPONENT_1>>

  // <<CHILD_COMPONENT_2>>

  // <<CHILD_COMPONENT_3>>

  return {
    component: AIPromptViewer,
    print: function () { window.print(); },
    refresh: function () { /* optional refresh logic */ }
  };
}
","componentName":"AIPromptViewer","componentType":"other","dataAccessType":"static","description":"A modern, pastel-themed interactive viewer that lets users browse AI prompts by categories/subcategories, view lists of prompts, and drill into prompt details in a clean, two-panel read-only interface.","callbackStrategy":"coordinated","stateStructure":{"selectedCategoryID":"Currently selected category or subcategory ID","selectedPromptID":"Currently selected prompt ID for detail view. Null if showing list.","sidebar":"State for the category navigation tree (e.g., expanded/collapsed nodes)","promptList":"State for the prompt list (e.g., scroll position, selection)","promptDetail":"State for the prompt detail view (e.g., drill-in navigation state)"},"childComponents":[{"placeholder":"CHILD_COMPONENT_1","componentName":"CategorySidebar","exampleUsage":"<CategorySidebar
  data={categories}
  config={{}}
  userState={fullUserState.sidebar || {}}
  onEvent={handleComponentEvent}
  styles={styles}
  callbacks={callbacks}
  utilities={utilities}
  statePath=\"sidebar\"
  selectedCategoryID={fullUserState.selectedCategoryID}
/>","description":"Displays a hierarchical tree of categories and subcategories for AI prompts in a sidebar. Uses the exact data structure from the provided categories (each with ID, Name, ParentID, Description). Renders as a collapsible/expandable tree, maintaining expand/collapse and selection state. When a category or subcategory is clicked, emits an itemSelected event with the selected category ID. Visual cues for selected node, hover, and expansion. If a node is expanded/collapsed, emits a stateChanged event so that the open/closed status is persistent. Adheres to the pastel, modern design system with readable fonts, visible focus, and whitespace. May allow search/filter in future, but not required. Accepts a selectedCategoryID prop for highlighting the active node. Handles empty state (no categories) gracefully.","statePath":"sidebar","components":[{"placeholder":"SUB_CHILD_COMPONENT_1","programmaticName":"TreeNode","description":"Represents a single node in the category tree, with logic for expand/collapse, selection, and recursion for child nodes. Handles click, keyboard, focus, and state updates. Receives its own node data, expanded/collapsed state, selected node ID, and emits selection or expansion events upward.","statePath":"treeNode","components":[],"componentCode":"function CategoryTreeNode({ data, styles, config, userState, statePath, onEvent, callbacks, utilities }) {
    // <<CATEGORY_TREE_NODE>> is NOT used here since this is the CategoryTreeNode component itself
    const { ID, Name, Children = [] } = data || {};
    // userState: { expanded: boolean }
    const [localState, setLocalState] = useState({
        expanded: !!(userState && userState.expanded),
        ...userState
    });

    // Selection comes from parent (selectedCategoryId or selectedPromptId)
    const selectedCategoryId = config?.selectedCategoryId;
    const focusedNodeId = config?.focusedNodeId;

    const isSelected = selectedCategoryId === ID;
    const isFocused = focusedNodeId === ID;
    const hasChildren = Array.isArray(Children) && Children.length > 0;

    // Keyboard navigation: Enter/Space to select, ArrowRight to expand, ArrowLeft to collapse, Up/Down for navigation (handled by parent tree)
    const nodeRef = React.useRef();

    // Sync local state with userState if userState changes externally
    React.useEffect(() => {
        setLocalState(ls => ({ ...ls, ...userState }));
    }, [userState]);

    // Expand/collapse toggle
    const handleExpandToggle = (e) => {
        e.stopPropagation();
        const newExpanded = !localState.expanded;
        const newState = { ...localState, expanded: newExpanded };
        setLocalState(newState);
        onEvent({
            type: 'stateChanged',
            source: 'CategoryTreeNode',
            payload: {
                statePath,
                newState
            },
            bubbles: true
        });
        onEvent({
            type: 'expandToggled',
            source: 'CategoryTreeNode',
            payload: {
                nodeId: ID,
                expanded: newExpanded
            },
            bubbles: true
        });
    };

    // Node selection
    const handleSelect = (e) => {
        e.stopPropagation();
        onEvent({
            type: 'itemSelected',
            source: 'CategoryTreeNode',
            payload: {
                itemId: ID,
                item: data,
                statePath
            },
            bubbles: true
        });
    };

    // Keyboard events
    const handleKeyDown = (e) => {
        if (e.key === 'ArrowRight' && hasChildren && !localState.expanded) {
            handleExpandToggle(e);
        } else if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft' && hasChildren && localState.expanded) {
            handleExpandToggle(e);
        } else if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
            handleSelect(e);
        }
        // Up/Down navigation is handled by parent (treeview focus mgmt)
    };

    // Focus visual
    const handleNodeFocus = () => {
        onEvent({
            type: 'nodeFocused',
            source: 'CategoryTreeNode',
            payload: {
                nodeId: ID,
                statePath
            },
            bubbles: true
        });
    };

    // Pastel node background
    const nodeBg = isSelected
        ? styles.colors.primary
        : isFocused
        ? styles.colors.surface
        : styles.colors.background;
    const nodeFg = isSelected ? '#fff' : styles.colors.text;

    // Indentation for hierarchy
    const level = config?.level || 0;
    const indent = level * 20;

    // Expand/collapse icon
    const iconStyle = {
        width: 24,
        height: 24,
        display: 'flex',
        alignItems: 'center',
        justifyContent: 'center',
        color: isSelected ? '#fff' : styles.colors.secondary,
        fontSize: styles.typography.fontSize.md,
        userSelect: 'none',
        cursor: 'pointer',
        marginRight: styles.spacing.xs
    };

    return (
        <div style={{
            paddingLeft: indent,
            display: 'flex',
            flexDirection: 'column',
            outline: isFocused ? `2px solid ${styles.colors.primary}` : 'none',
            background: nodeBg,
            color: nodeFg,
            borderRadius: styles.borders.radius,
            marginBottom: styles.spacing.xs,
            boxShadow: isSelected ? `0 2px 8px 0 rgba(33,150,243,0.09)` : 'none',
            transition: 'background 0.18s',
            minHeight: 36
        }}>
            <div
                ref={nodeRef}
                tabIndex={0}
                aria-selected={isSelected}
                aria-expanded={hasChildren ? localState.expanded : undefined}
                aria-label={Name}
                role=\"treeitem\"
                style={{
                    display: 'flex',
                    alignItems: 'center',
                    cursor: 'pointer',
                    fontFamily: styles.typography.fontFamily,
                    fontSize: styles.typography.fontSize.md,
                    fontWeight: isSelected ? 600 : 400,
                    minHeight: 36,
                    outline: 'none',
                    padding: `${styles.spacing.xs} ${styles.spacing.sm}`,
                    border: isSelected ? `1px solid ${styles.colors.primaryHover}` : '1px solid transparent',
                    boxSizing: 'border-box',
                    borderRadius: styles.borders.radius,
                }}
                onClick={handleSelect}
                onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}
                onFocus={handleNodeFocus}
            >
                {hasChildren && (
                    <button
                        onClick={handleExpandToggle}
                        tabIndex={-1}
                        aria-label={localState.expanded ? 'Collapse category' : 'Expand category'}
                        style={iconStyle}
                    >
                        {localState.expanded ? (
                            <span style={{fontWeight: 900, fontSize: '18px'}}>â€“</span>
                        ) : (
                            <span style={{fontWeight: 900, fontSize: '18px'}}>+</span>
                        )}
                    </button>
                )}
                <span style={{
                    flex: 1,
                    overflow: 'hidden',
                    textOverflow: 'ellipsis',
                    whiteSpace: 'nowrap',
                }}>{Name}</span>
            </div>
            {hasChildren && localState.expanded && (
                <div role=\"group\" style={{ marginLeft: styles.spacing.sm }}>
                    {Children.map((child) => (
                        <CategoryTreeNode
                            key={child.ID}
                            data={child}
                            config={{
                                ...config,
                                level: level + 1,
                                selectedCategoryId,
                                focusedNodeId
                            }}
                            userState={userState?.[child.ID] || {}}
                            onEvent={onEvent}
                            styles={styles}
                            callbacks={callbacks}
                            utilities={utilities}
                            statePath={`${statePath}.${child.ID}`}
                        />
                    ))}
                </div>
            )}
        </div>
    );
}
"}],"componentCode":"function CategorySidebar({ data, config, userState, onEvent, styles, callbacks, utilities, statePath, selectedCategoryID }) {
    // Placeholder for any sub-components (none specified here)

    // ---- Helpers ----
    // Build tree from flat category list
    const buildCategoryTree = (categories) => {
        // Map of ID to node
        const nodesById = {};
        // Root nodes (no ParentID)
        const roots = [];
        (categories || []).forEach(cat => {
            nodesById[cat.ID] = { ...cat, children: [] };
        });
        (categories || []).forEach(cat => {
            if (cat.ParentID && nodesById[cat.ParentID]) {
                nodesById[cat.ParentID].children.push(nodesById[cat.ID]);
            } else {
                roots.push(nodesById[cat.ID]);
            }
        });
        return roots;
    };

    // ---- State ----
    // State shape: { expanded: { [categoryId]: true }, lastSelectedId: string }
    const [localState, setLocalState] = React.useState({
        expanded: {}, // categoryID: true/false
        lastSelectedId: selectedCategoryID || null,
        ...userState
    });

    // Keep highlight in sync if selectedCategoryID changes from parent
    React.useEffect(() => {
        if (selectedCategoryID && selectedCategoryID !== localState.lastSelectedId) {
            setLocalState(prev => ({ ...prev, lastSelectedId: selectedCategoryID }));
        }
    }, [selectedCategoryID]);

    // ---- Event Emitters ----
    const updateState = (updates) => {
        const newState = { ...localState, ...updates };
        setLocalState(newState);
        onEvent({
            type: 'stateChanged',
            source: 'CategorySidebar',
            payload: { statePath, newState },
            bubbles: true
        });
    };

    const handleSelect = (categoryId) => {
        updateState({ lastSelectedId: categoryId });
        onEvent({
            type: 'itemSelected',
            source: 'CategorySidebar',
            payload: { itemId: categoryId },
            bubbles: true
        });
    };

    const handleExpandToggle = (categoryId) => {
        const expanded = { ...localState.expanded, [categoryId]: !localState.expanded[categoryId] };
        updateState({ expanded });
        onEvent({
            type: 'stateChanged',
            source: 'CategorySidebar',
            payload: { statePath, newState: { ...localState, expanded } },
            bubbles: true
        });
    };

    // ---- Renderers ----
    // Recursively render the tree
    const renderTree = (nodes, depth = 0) => {
        if (!nodes || nodes.length === 0) return null;
        return nodes.map(node => {
            const isExpanded = !!localState.expanded[node.ID];
            const isSelected = localState.lastSelectedId === node.ID;
            const hasChildren = node.children && node.children.length > 0;
            return (
                <React.Fragment key={node.ID}>
                    <div
                        tabIndex={0}
                        aria-selected={isSelected}
                        onClick={() => handleSelect(node.ID)}
                        onKeyDown={e => {
                            if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') handleSelect(node.ID);
                        }}
                        style={{
                            display: 'flex',
                            alignItems: 'center',
                            padding: `${styles.spacing.xs} ${styles.spacing.md}`,
                            paddingLeft: `calc(${styles.spacing.md} + ${depth * 24}px)`,
                            background: isSelected ? styles.colors.primary : 'transparent',
                            color: isSelected ? '#fff' : styles.colors.text,
                            borderRadius: styles.borders.radius,
                            marginBottom: styles.spacing.xs,
                            cursor: 'pointer',
                            outline: 'none',
                            fontFamily: styles.typography.fontFamily,
                            fontSize: styles.typography.fontSize.md,
                            transition: 'background 0.15s',
                            boxShadow: isSelected ? `0 0 0 2px ${styles.colors.primaryHover}` : 'none',
                        }}
                        onMouseEnter={e => {
                            if (!isSelected) e.currentTarget.style.background = styles.colors.surface;
                        }}
                        onMouseLeave={e => {
                            if (!isSelected) e.currentTarget.style.background = 'transparent';
                        }}
                        onFocus={e => {
                            if (!isSelected) e.currentTarget.style.boxShadow = `0 0 0 2px ${styles.colors.primaryHover}`;
                        }}
                        onBlur={e => {
                            if (!isSelected) e.currentTarget.style.boxShadow = 'none';
                        }}
                    >
                        {hasChildren && (
                            <button
                                aria-label={isExpanded ? 'Collapse category' : 'Expand category'}
                                tabIndex={-1}
                                onClick={e => { e.stopPropagation(); handleExpandToggle(node.ID); }}
                                style={{
                                    background: 'none',
                                    border: 'none',
                                    color: isSelected ? '#fff' : styles.colors.textSecondary,
                                    cursor: 'pointer',
                                    fontSize: styles.typography.fontSize.md,
                                    marginRight: styles.spacing.sm,
                                    outline: 'none',
                                    width: 24,
                                    height: 24,
                                    display: 'flex',
                                    alignItems: 'center',
                                    justifyContent: 'center',
                                    borderRadius: styles.borders.radius,
                                    transition: 'background 0.12s',
                                }}
                                onMouseEnter={e => e.currentTarget.style.background = styles.colors.surface}
                                onMouseLeave={e => e.currentTarget.style.background = 'none'}
                            >
                                {isExpanded ? (
                                    <span aria-hidden=\"true\" style={{ fontSize: 16 }}>?</span>
                                ) : (
                                    <span aria-hidden=\"true\" style={{ fontSize: 16 }}>?</span>
                                )}
                            </button>
                        )}
                        <span style={{
                            fontWeight: isSelected ? 600 : 400,
                            overflow: 'hidden',
                            textOverflow: 'ellipsis',
                            whiteSpace: 'nowrap',
                        }}>{node.Name}</span>
                    </div>
                    {hasChildren && isExpanded && (
                        <div>
                            {renderTree(node.children, depth + 1)}
                        </div>
                    )}
                </React.Fragment>
            );
        });
    };

    // ---- Main Render ----
    const categories = Array.isArray(data) ? data : (Array.isArray(data?.categories) ? data.categories : []);
    const tree = buildCategoryTree(categories);
    const empty = !categories || categories.length === 0;

    return (
        <div
            style={{
                height: '100%',
                display: 'flex',
                flexDirection: 'column',
                background: styles.colors.background,
                borderRight: `${styles.borders.width} solid ${styles.colors.border}`,
                padding: styles.spacing.md,
                minWidth: 240,
                maxWidth: 400,
                overflowY: 'auto',
                fontFamily: styles.typography.fontFamily,
            }}
        >
            <div style={{
                fontSize: styles.typography.fontSize.lg,
                fontWeight: 600,
                color: styles.colors.text,
                marginBottom: styles.spacing.lg,
                letterSpacing: '0.01em',
                textAlign: 'left',
            }}>Categories</div>
            {empty ? (
                <div style={{
                    color: styles.colors.textSecondary,
                    textAlign: 'center',
                    padding: styles.spacing.xl,
                    fontSize: styles.typography.fontSize.md
                }}>
                    <div style={{fontSize: '36px', opacity: 0.25, marginBottom: styles.spacing.md}}>??</div>
                    <div>No categories available</div>
                </div>
            ) : (
                <div style={{ flex: 1 }}>{renderTree(tree)}</div>
            )}
        </div>
    );
}
"},{"placeholder":"CHILD_COMPONENT_2","componentName":"PromptList","exampleUsage":"<PromptList
  data={filteredPrompts}
