{"responsePhase":"analysis_complete","techExplanation":"This component uses a coordinated event system and hierarchical userState to manage navigation and selection. The sidebar is always visible and includes a visually distinct 'Uncategorized' node (with a special ID and icon), letting users switch between categories and uncategorized prompts at any time. The main panel filters prompts accordingly. All data is static/in-memory. The UI overrides theme colors with Canadian and Rasta color blocks, gradients, and icons. Child components receive data, config (including uncategorizedId/icon), userState, and statePath for proper event bubbling and state persistence.","userExplanation":"Browse AI prompts by category or see all 'Uncategorized' prompts at any time! Use the left sidebar (with bold red maple leafs and reggae colors) to pick a category or the uncategorized option. Prompts appear as energetic, colorful cardsâ€”click any to see full details. Enjoy the lively Canadian and Rasta look as you explore.","componentOptions":[{"AIRank":1,"AIRankExplanation":"","option":{"functionalRequirements":"This component is an interactive, read-only viewer for AI prompts where users can browse prompts by categories or view those without a category ('Uncategorized'). The interface is split into two panels: a sidebar for navigating categories (including a persistent, clearly marked 'Uncategorized' option) and a main panel showing either a list of prompts for the selected category or detailed information for a selected prompt. The sidebar always displays 'Uncategorized' at the top or bottom, with a unique visual icon. Selecting 'Uncategorized' shows all prompts without a CategoryID in the main panel. Users can drill in to prompt details and back out to the list. The entire UI uses vibrant Canadian (reds, whites, maple leafs) and Rasta (greens, yellows, reds) themes for a bold, playful, energetic look, while maintaining good readability and accessibility. All data is static/in-memory, and empty states are handled gracefully.","technicalDesign":"The root component manages overall state: selectedCategoryID (null for 'Uncategorized'), selectedPromptID, and child component state for sidebar, list, and detail. The sidebar displays a hierarchical tree of categories with a persistent 'Uncategorized' node (always visible, visually distinct with icon/decoration), using the exact property names from data. Selecting any node updates selectedCategoryID; selecting 'Uncategorized' sets selectedCategoryID to a special value (e.g., null or '__UNCATEGORIZED__'). The main panel filters prompts accordingly: for a category, shows prompts with matching CategoryID; for 'Uncategorized', shows prompts where CategoryID is null/missing. Clicking a prompt drills in to details, which display Name, Description, Status, CreatedAt, UpdatedAt. All interactions are accessible by mouse and keyboard. All styling leverages the provided styles object, but is overridden/augmented to inject Canadian and Rasta colors, gradients, and motifs throughout the UI (sidebar backgrounds, icons, headers, selected states). Event handling is coordinated via a standard handler, with state updates persisted at each level. Empty states in both sidebar and main panel show fun, themed messages/icons. Data is always static/in-memory, and all child components use hierarchical userState and coordinated event handling.","componentCode":"function createComponent(React, ReactDOM, useState, useEffect, useCallback, createStateUpdater, createStandardEventHandler) {
  'use strict';

  function AIPromptViewerCanadianRasta({ data, utilities, userState, callbacks, styles }) {
