}"}],"title":"AI Prompt Viewer (Rasta Canadian Edition)","userExplanation":"Browse AI prompts by categories or quickly see all prompts without a category using the 'Uncategorized' option. Click any prompt to view its details, then use the back button to return. The interface is full of Canadian and Rasta colors for a lively, fun experience. Navigation is easy with both mouse and keyboard.","techExplanation":"The root component manages the selected category (including a special 'Uncategorized' node) and selected prompt, and routes events from child components via a coordinated event handler. The sidebar always shows a distinct 'Uncategorized' node, using a special ID, and passes this to the main panel for filtering. All filtering is done in-memory. All components receive hierarchical userState and style props, with bold color themes and icons passed via config for maximal Canadian/Rasta flair. Accessibility and keyboard navigation are enforced. No dynamic data access is required; all data is static and filtered client-side."}},{"AIRank":3,"AIRankExplanation":"","option":{"functionalRequirements":"This interactive AI Prompts viewer allows users to browse prompts by hierarchical category and also always access all 'Uncategorized' prompts (those not assigned to any category) via a special, persistent sidebar option. The interface uses a two-panel layout: the left sidebar is a tree of categories and subcategories (with expand/collapse), and always shows an 'Uncategorized' node with a distinct visual cue. The right panel shows either a list of prompts in the selected category (or all uncategorized prompts if 'Uncategorized' is selected), or a detail view for a selected prompt. Users can freely switch between any category and 'Uncategorized' and drill into prompt details with a back button to return. The UI is themed with bold Canadian (reds, whites, maple leaves) and Rasta (greens, yellows, reds) colors/motifs for a lively, energetic look, while maintaining readability and accessibility. All interactions are accessible by mouse and keyboard, and the component handles empty states gracefully. All data is static/in-memory; filtering is done client-side.","technicalDesign":"The root component manages fullUserState, including selectedCategoryID (null or a category's ID, or the special value '__UNCATEGORIZED__'), selectedPromptID for drill-in, and userState slices for the sidebar, prompt list, and detail view. The sidebar always displays a hierarchical tree of categories with an additional persistent 'Uncategorized' node (placed at the top or bottom), visually distinct with a custom icon or color treatment (e.g., a maple leaf with reggae accents). Clicking a category or 'Uncategorized' emits an itemSelected event; selection is tracked for clear visual feedback. The main panel filters prompts: if a category is selected, shows prompts with that CategoryID; if 'Uncategorized' is selected (CategoryID null/missing), shows all such prompts; if a prompt is selected, shows its details. Drill-in/drill-out is handled with coordinated events. The component applies a vibrant Canadian/Rasta theme throughout (sidebar, cards, buttons, accents), with gradients, icons, and color blocks as appropriate. State is hierarchical (child state slices by key) and managed by coordinated event handling. All property access uses exact casing from the data.","componentCode":"function createComponent(React, ReactDOM, useState, useEffect, useCallback, createStateUpdater, createStandardEventHandler) {
  'use strict';

  function AIPromptViewer({ data, utilities, userState, callbacks, styles }) {
    // State: selectedCategoryID, selectedPromptID, plus child states
    const [fullUserState, setFullUserState] = useState({
      selectedCategoryID: null, // category ID or '__UNCATEGORIZED__'
      selectedPromptID: null,
      sidebar: {},
      promptList: {},
      promptDetail: {},
      ...userState
    });

    const updateUserState = (stateUpdate) => {
      const newState = { ...fullUserState, ...stateUpdate };
      setFullUserState(newState);
      if (callbacks?.UpdateUserState) {
        callbacks.UpdateUserState(newState);
      }
    };

    // Centralized event handler
    const handleComponentEvent = (event) => {
      if (event.type === 'itemSelected' && event.source === 'CategorySidebar') {
        updateUserState({
          selectedCategoryID: event.payload.itemId,
          selectedPromptID: null,
          sidebar: event.payload.newState || fullUserState.sidebar
        });
        return;
      }
      if (event.type === 'itemSelected' && event.source === 'PromptList') {
        updateUserState({
          selectedPromptID: event.payload.itemId,
          promptList: event.payload.newState || fullUserState.promptList
        });
        return;
      }
      if ((event.type === 'actionTriggered' && event.payload?.action === 'back' && event.source === 'PromptDetail') || (event.type === 'drillOut' && event.source === 'PromptDetail')) {
        updateUserState({
          selectedPromptID: null
        });
        return;
      }
      const standardHandler = createStandardEventHandler(updateUserState, callbacks);
      standardHandler(event);
    };

    // Data extraction
    const categories = data?.data_item_0 || [];
    const prompts = data?.data_item_1 || [];

    // Special value for uncategorized
    const UNCATEGORIZED_ID = '__UNCATEGORIZED__';
    // Determine which prompts to show
    const filteredPrompts = prompts.filter(p => {
      if (fullUserState.selectedCategoryID === UNCATEGORIZED_ID) {
        return !p.CategoryID || p.CategoryID === null;
      } else if (fullUserState.selectedCategoryID) {
        return p.CategoryID === fullUserState.selectedCategoryID;
      }
      return false;
    });
    // Prompt selected?
    const selectedPrompt = prompts.find(p => p.ID === fullUserState.selectedPromptID);

    // Custom Canadian/Rasta sidebar background (vivid gradient)
    const sidebarBg = 'linear-gradient(135deg, #d32d2f 0%, #fff 40%, #18ab3b 75%, #fcc419 100%)';

    return (
      <div
        style={{
          display: 'flex',
          height: '100%',
          background: styles.colors.background,
          fontFamily: styles.typography.fontFamily
        }}
      >
        {/* Sidebar */}
        <div
          style={{
            width: '320px',
            minWidth: '220px',
            maxWidth: '380px',
            background: sidebarBg,
            borderRight: `${styles.borders.width} solid ${styles.colors.border}`,
            padding: 0,
            boxSizing: 'border-box',
            overflow: 'auto',
            height: '100%',
            display: 'flex',
            flexDirection: 'column',
            position: 'relative'
          }}
        >
          <CategorySidebar
            data={categories}
            config={{
              uncategorizedNode: {
                id: UNCATEGORIZED_ID,
                label: 'Uncategorized',
                icon: '??', // Maple leaf (Canadian) with reggae colors by styling in child
                // Position: 'top' or 'bottom', let's use bottom for visual weight
                position: 'bottom'
              }
            }}
            userState={fullUserState.sidebar || {}}
            onEvent={handleComponentEvent}
            styles={styles}
            callbacks={callbacks}
            utilities={utilities}
            statePath=\"sidebar\"
            selectedCategoryID={fullUserState.selectedCategoryID}
          />
        </div>
        {/* Main panel */}
        <div
          style={{
            flex: 1,
            overflow: 'auto',
            padding: styles.spacing.lg,
            background: 'linear-gradient(122deg,#fff 0%,#e53935 33%,#fcc419 66%,#18ab3b 100%)',
            minHeight: '100%',
            display: 'flex',
            flexDirection: 'column',
            position: 'relative'
          }}
        >
          {/* Fun Header Bar with Canadian/Rasta icons */}
          <div style={{
            display: 'flex',
            alignItems: 'center',
            gap: styles.spacing.md,
            marginBottom: styles.spacing.xl,
            background: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.95)',
            borderRadius: styles.borders.radius,
            boxShadow: '0 2px 12px rgba(220,38,38,0.07)',
            padding: `${styles.spacing.sm} ${styles.spacing.lg}`,
            fontWeight: 700,
            fontSize: styles.typography.fontSize.xl,
            letterSpacing: '0.02em',
            color: '#d32d2f',
            textShadow: '0 2px 8px #fff'
          }}>
            <span role=\"img\" aria-label=\"Maple\">??</span>
            <span style={{
              background: 'linear-gradient(90deg,#d32d2f 0%,#fcc419 40%,#18ab3b 100%)',
              WebkitBackgroundClip: 'text',
              WebkitTextFillColor: 'transparent',
              fontWeight: 900,
              fontSize: styles.typography.fontSize.xl,
              letterSpacing: '0.03em',
            }}>Prompt Carnival</span>
            <span role=\"img\" aria-label=\"Rasta\">??????</span>
          </div>
          {!selectedPrompt && (
            <PromptList
              data={filteredPrompts}
              config={{
                theme: 'canadian-rasta',
                uncategorizedSelected: fullUserState.selectedCategoryID === UNCATEGORIZED_ID
              }}
              userState={fullUserState.promptList || {}}
              onEvent={handleComponentEvent}
              styles={styles}
              callbacks={callbacks}
              utilities={utilities}
              statePath=\"promptList\"
              selectedPromptID={fullUserState.selectedPromptID}
            />
          )}
          {selectedPrompt && (
            <PromptDetail
              data={selectedPrompt}
              config={{ theme: 'canadian-rasta' }}
              userState={fullUserState.promptDetail || {}}
              onEvent={handleComponentEvent}
              styles={styles}
              callbacks={callbacks}
              utilities={utilities}
              statePath=\"promptDetail\"
            />
          )}
        </div>
      </div>
    );
  }

  // <<CHILD_COMPONENT_1>>

  // <<CHILD_COMPONENT_2>>

  // <<CHILD_COMPONENT_3>>

  return {
    component: AIPromptViewer,
    print: function () { window.print(); },
    refresh: function () { /* optional refresh logic */ }
  };
}
","componentName":"AIPromptViewer","componentType":"other","dataAccessType":"static","description":"An interactive, visually vibrant viewer for AI prompts with a two-panel layout: a sidebar for navigating categories (including a persistent 'Uncategorized' node) and a main panel for listing prompts or showing prompt details. The theme is a bold, energetic fusion of Canadian and Rasta colors and motifs.","callbackStrategy":"coordinated","stateStructure":{"selectedCategoryID":"Currently selected category, subcategory, or '__UNCATEGORIZED__' for uncategorized prompts","selectedPromptID":"Currently selected prompt ID for detail view. Null if showing list.","sidebar":"State for the category navigation tree (e.g., expanded/collapsed nodes, last selection)","promptList":"State for the prompt list (focus, selection, scroll, etc.)","promptDetail":"State for the prompt detail view (e.g., drill-in navigation state)"},"childComponents":[{"placeholder":"CHILD_COMPONENT_1","componentName":"CategorySidebar","exampleUsage":"<CategorySidebar
